# Auto Profile Picture Extension - Project Architecture

This is a Mozilla Thunderbird extension that automatically fetches and displays profile pictures for email senders.

## Core Architecture

### Entry Points

- [background.js](mdc:src/background.js) - Main extension entry point, initializes all services
- [manifest.json](mdc:src/manifest.json) - Extension manifest (version 2.4.0+, requires TB 112.0+)

### Service Layer (`src/src/`)

Core services follow a single-responsibility pattern:

- [AvatarService.js](mdc:src/src/AvatarService.js) - Manages avatar URLs with session caching
- [ProfilePictureFetcher.js](mdc:src/src/ProfilePictureFetcher.js) - Fetches avatars using provider strategies
- [MailService.js](mdc:src/src/MailService.js) - Handles email-related operations
- [ContactsService.js](mdc:src/src/ContactsService.js) - Manages Thunderbird contacts integration
- [MessagesService.js](mdc:src/src/MessagesService.js) - Processes email messages
- [CacheStorage.js](mdc:src/src/CacheStorage.js) - Persistent storage management using browser.storage
- [ImageConverter.js](mdc:src/src/ImageConverter.js) - Converts images to data URLs
- [Author.js](mdc:src/src/Author.js) - Represents email author with parsing utilities
- [RecipientInitial.js](mdc:src/src/RecipientInitial.js) - Generates initials when no avatar available

### Provider Pattern (`src/providers/`)

Avatar providers implement the [Provider.js](mdc:src/providers/Provider.js) base class:

- [ProviderFactory.js](mdc:src/providers/ProviderFactory.js) - Creates provider instances based on settings
- Each provider (Gravatar, Google, BIMI, etc.) implements `async getUrl(author)`
- Providers have a `scope` property: `Scope.DOMAIN` or `Scope.EMAIL`

### Strategy Pattern (`src/src/strategies/`)

Multiple strategies for avatar fetching:

- [AvatarStrategy.js](mdc:src/src/strategies/AvatarStrategy.js) - Base strategy class
- [CacheStrategy.js](mdc:src/src/strategies/CacheStrategy.js) - Check cache first
- [ContactsStrategy.js](mdc:src/src/strategies/ContactsStrategy.js) - Check Thunderbird contacts
- [OnlineStrategy.js](mdc:src/src/strategies/OnlineStrategy.js) - Fetch from providers
- [VoidStrategy.js](mdc:src/src/strategies/VoidStrategy.js) - Fallback to initials

### Experiment API (`src/api/`)

- [headerApi.js](mdc:src/api/headerApi.js) - Custom WebExtension API for UI modifications
- [headerApi.json](mdc:src/api/headerApi.json) - API schema definition
- Handles rendering avatars in mail headers, inbox list, and conversation views

### Settings Management (`src/settings/`)

- [SettingsManager.js](mdc:src/settings/SettingsManager.js) - Manages extension settings
- [defaultSettings.js](mdc:src/settings/defaultSettings.js) - Default configuration values
- [options/](mdc:src/settings/options/) - Settings UI (HTML/JS/CSS)

## Thunderbird Version Compatibility

### CSP Compliance

Thunderbird 145 introduced stricter Content Security Policy that broke data URL usage in img elements. TB 146 fixed this issue. The extension uses conditional rendering:

- **TB 145 only**: Canvas with `createImageBitmap()` for CSP-safe image rendering (workaround)
- **TB < 145 and TB 146+**: Traditional `<img>` elements with data URLs (standard approach)

### Version Detection

- Privileged context (headerApi.js): Uses `Services.appinfo.version`
- Extension context (options.js): Uses `browser.runtime.getBrowserInfo()`
- Default fallback: Assumes TB 145 (canvas approach for safety)

## Key Design Patterns

1. **Service Pattern**: Core functionality isolated in service classes
2. **Provider Pattern**: Pluggable avatar providers
3. **Strategy Pattern**: Composable avatar fetching strategies
4. **Factory Pattern**: Provider instantiation
5. **Caching**: Two-tier caching (session cache + persistent storage)

## Module System

- Uses ES6 modules (`type: "module"` in package.json)
- All imports use `.js` extensions
- No bundler - native ES modules in Thunderbird

## Testing

- Test framework: Mocha + Chai
- Tests located in `test/src/`
- Run with `npm test`
- Tests cover Author parsing, MailService, and RecipientInitial logic
